02:03.324 --> 02:05.058
WOMAN: Was it a robbery?

02:05.159 --> 02:06.560
**

02:06.660 --> 02:08.896
Hey. Hey.
Are you Ronny?

02:08.996 --> 02:10.198
Stay the fuck away from me.

02:10.298 --> 02:11.499
I'm trying to help you.

02:11.599 --> 02:12.966
What do you want?
I'm Dr. Chance --

02:13.066 --> 02:14.702
I don't know who the fuck
that is, okay?

02:14.802 --> 02:17.238
Look.
I'm Josefa's therapist

02:17.338 --> 02:18.906
at the Victims
of Violent Crimes Unit.

02:19.006 --> 02:20.741
You know what that is?

02:20.841 --> 02:23.244
(sirens wailing)
Don't run!

02:23.344 --> 02:24.878
Ronny, don't run.
They'll think you're guilty.

02:24.978 --> 02:26.214
Just stay where you are.

02:26.314 --> 02:27.548
I didn't do this, man!

02:27.648 --> 02:29.250
I didn't do this, okay?!
I --

02:29.350 --> 02:30.484
She was my wife.
I loved her!

02:30.584 --> 02:32.386
I-I did stuff, okay?

02:32.486 --> 02:33.654
I did stuff, but I ain't
no fucking murderer, man.

02:33.754 --> 02:34.755
I know. I know.

02:34.855 --> 02:35.823
I know you didn't do it,
Ronny.

02:35.923 --> 02:36.924
But you just got to
let me help you.

02:37.024 --> 02:39.327
Where were you?
Where you in the building?

02:39.427 --> 02:40.728
Fuck.
I'm so fucked, man.

02:40.828 --> 02:41.929
OFFICER: Hey!
Don't move.

02:42.029 --> 02:43.497
CHANCE:
You got to tell me quick.

02:43.597 --> 02:45.366
We don't have a lot of time.
Tell me where you were.
OFFICER: Hey!

02:45.466 --> 02:46.367
I'm so fucked.
I'm so fucked.

02:46.467 --> 02:48.402
Put your hands up.
You the husband?

02:48.502 --> 02:50.704
-Uh, yeah.
-We're just talking, Officer.

02:50.804 --> 02:53.040
-Who are you?
-Josefa Pefaur's therapist.

02:53.140 --> 02:55.576
Detectives need to speak to you,
Ronny. Come on, now. Let's go.

02:55.676 --> 02:56.577
RONNY: What,
I-I'm under arrest?

02:56.677 --> 02:59.247
It's up to you.
Y-You're being detained.

02:59.347 --> 03:00.514
What? Hey!

03:00.614 --> 03:02.550
What? I-I didn't do anything!
What?

03:02.650 --> 03:05.519
Detectives gonna want
to speak to you, too.

03:05.619 --> 03:06.520
**

03:06.620 --> 03:08.789
Did Mrs. Pefaur
ever tell you

03:08.889 --> 03:10.724
that her husband
had threatened to kill her?

03:10.824 --> 03:12.059
No.

03:12.159 --> 03:14.228
"No, not in those words,"
or...

03:14.328 --> 03:18.766
Just no.
She -- Uh, in no words, no.

03:18.866 --> 03:20.534
(telephone rings)

03:20.634 --> 03:22.270
Did she ever say
she was worried

03:22.370 --> 03:24.037
her husband might kill her?

03:25.706 --> 03:27.875
Does Ronny Pefaur have
an alibi?

03:27.975 --> 03:29.543
Is that a "no"?

03:29.643 --> 03:32.045
**

03:32.145 --> 03:34.615
(sighs)

03:34.715 --> 03:36.650
**

03:36.750 --> 03:38.586
**

03:38.686 --> 03:40.888
Plenty more
where this came from.

03:40.988 --> 03:42.590
**

03:42.690 --> 03:45.158
Yeah, I know.
I know what Josefa went through.

03:45.259 --> 03:47.227
And I know "addressing
the welfare of the patient"

03:47.328 --> 03:49.963
means protecting
confidentiality in perpetuity,

03:50.063 --> 03:51.499
but right now,

03:51.599 --> 03:53.967
a lady who everybody's saying
was kind of an angel

03:54.067 --> 03:57.905
is dead with her head
almost cut off.

03:58.005 --> 03:59.573
So here we are.

03:59.673 --> 04:01.809
Ronny Pefaur's alibi is

04:01.909 --> 04:03.311
he says
he was playing cards

04:03.411 --> 04:06.246
with some friends
at a chop shop in Bayview.

04:06.347 --> 04:07.448
You don't believe him?

04:07.548 --> 04:10.651
You know what, Doc?
I really don't.

04:10.751 --> 04:13.153
But how 'bout you tell me
why you seem to?

04:13.253 --> 04:15.856
(siren wails)

04:15.956 --> 04:18.692
I...

04:18.792 --> 04:21.261
I have another patient

04:21.362 --> 04:23.664
who was in group therapy
with Mrs. Pefaur.

04:23.764 --> 04:26.800
Now, recently, I gave him
a projective psychological test

04:26.900 --> 04:28.602
involving
interpreting images.

04:28.702 --> 04:31.004
When I saw Josefa's body,

04:31.104 --> 04:32.105
it was posed --

04:32.205 --> 04:34.675
it was posed exactly
like one of the images.

04:34.775 --> 04:36.877
I can get you a copy.

04:36.977 --> 04:38.546
This patient --

04:38.646 --> 04:41.148
if I run him, am I gonna find
any violent priors --

04:41.248 --> 04:43.984
assault, rape, abuse?

04:44.084 --> 04:46.019
(sighs)
No.

04:46.119 --> 04:47.888
Okay.

04:47.988 --> 04:50.358
Has he ever said he was going
to kill Mrs. Pefaur?

04:50.458 --> 04:53.961
No.

04:54.061 --> 04:56.464
Has he ever said he was gonna
kill a woman, kill anybody?

04:56.564 --> 04:59.199
No, I -- No.

04:59.299 --> 05:00.434
Okay.

05:00.534 --> 05:02.636
What we're left with, then,
is a feeling in your gut

05:02.736 --> 05:04.838
that something kind of looks
like something else.

05:04.938 --> 05:05.839
**

05:05.939 --> 05:08.976
Put up against a guy
on probation for battery

05:09.076 --> 05:12.012
with a history
of beating his wife,

05:12.112 --> 05:14.147
whose neighbors
called 911 on him for her

05:14.247 --> 05:17.050
26 times in 3 years.

05:17.150 --> 05:18.419
**

05:18.519 --> 05:20.354
You've got your gut, Doc,
and I've got mine.

05:20.454 --> 05:23.256
And here,
mine's the one that matters.

05:23.357 --> 05:24.992
**

05:25.092 --> 05:28.762
(siren wails)

05:28.862 --> 05:31.832
(horn honks, construction
equipment rattling in distance)

05:33.567 --> 05:35.503
**

05:35.603 --> 05:37.270
HYNES: The truth is
the job won't let me take

05:37.371 --> 05:41.041
this sick, murdering fuck
down the aboveboard way,

05:41.141 --> 05:43.076
so I'm doing
what needs to be done.

05:43.176 --> 05:44.612
WINTER: I envy you.
(sniffling)

05:44.712 --> 05:47.748
At least you know
who to be scared of.

05:47.848 --> 05:49.917
-You must get tired.
-You need my trust.

05:50.017 --> 05:51.952
Talking about this
so much...

05:52.052 --> 05:53.921
And I want
to give it to you.
...nothing changes.

05:54.021 --> 05:55.956
HYNES: You don't know
what you're doing.

05:56.056 --> 05:58.058
(bus horn blares)

05:59.292 --> 06:05.966
