18:14.294 --> 18:15.762
I ordered a PET scan.

18:15.862 --> 18:18.498
Allows us to look
at the glucose uptake

18:18.598 --> 18:21.868
or metabolism in the different
areas of the brain.

18:21.968 --> 18:23.636
You see that area there?

18:23.736 --> 18:28.341
It's the cingulate gyrus,
part of the limbic system.

18:28.441 --> 18:29.942
WINTER:
What about it?

18:30.042 --> 18:31.311
Well,
it's pretty interesting.

18:31.411 --> 18:34.947
Hypermetabolism in the front
part of the cingulate

18:35.047 --> 18:37.016
correlates
to obsessional thinking.

18:37.116 --> 18:41.020
Hypometabolism,
low glucose uptake,

18:41.120 --> 18:43.456
suggests
a lack of empathy.

18:43.556 --> 18:44.724
We're basically talking
about the way

18:44.824 --> 18:47.126
that ideas and emotions
link up.

18:47.227 --> 18:48.861
**

18:48.961 --> 18:52.532
And this is related
to decision-making?

18:52.632 --> 18:53.800
Yeah.

18:53.900 --> 18:55.968
Impulse control.

18:56.068 --> 18:59.138
Impulse control.
Okay.

18:59.239 --> 19:01.708
So, what does this show,
exactly?

19:01.808 --> 19:04.211
Well, it suggests, maybe,

19:04.311 --> 19:06.179
a certain lack of empathy

19:06.279 --> 19:10.683
combined with a need
to take control.

19:10.783 --> 19:13.686
**

19:13.786 --> 19:16.523
An ability to take risks,
do dangerous things

19:16.623 --> 19:18.725
while remaining
emotionally detached.

19:18.825 --> 19:19.759
**

19:19.859 --> 19:23.029
Kind of sangfroid
with attention to detail.

19:23.129 --> 19:26.366
And this is a result
of my attack?

19:26.466 --> 19:29.001
No. This is the brain
you were born with.
Hold on.

19:29.101 --> 19:33.440
It sounds like
you're describing a psychopath.

19:33.540 --> 19:35.408
**

19:35.508 --> 19:37.544
All this does is
it just shows a proclivity

19:37.644 --> 19:38.611
for certain kinds
of behavior.

19:38.711 --> 19:40.680
(scoffs)
It's just science.

19:40.780 --> 19:42.882
All the events
and experiences we have,

19:42.982 --> 19:45.418
they also shape
who and what we become.

19:45.518 --> 19:47.019
It's not just nature.

19:47.119 --> 19:49.088
You also need some...

19:49.188 --> 19:53.526
destructive nurturing
to become a psychopath.

19:53.626 --> 19:57.397
So...it's not my fault.
(sighs)

19:57.497 --> 20:00.433
I mean, it's not my fault
if I was born this way.

20:00.533 --> 20:02.235
