20:15.315 --> 20:16.549
I'd say that's possible.

20:16.649 --> 20:18.651
**

20:18.751 --> 20:20.119
Can I ask you something?

20:20.219 --> 20:23.923
Um, I'm a open book,
apparently.

20:24.023 --> 20:25.792
(chuckles)

20:25.892 --> 20:28.094
Are there things
you've done,

20:28.194 --> 20:31.998
things -- things
that you don't understand,

20:32.098 --> 20:33.500
things that make you go,
"Why?

20:33.600 --> 20:34.767
Where did that come from?"

20:34.867 --> 20:36.969
(horn honks)

20:37.069 --> 20:38.605
**

20:38.705 --> 20:41.274
Bad things, you mean?

20:41.374 --> 20:42.742
**

20:42.842 --> 20:45.312
Not necessarily.

20:45.412 --> 20:46.413
Our moral decisions

20:46.513 --> 20:49.115
are essentially
emotional decisions.

20:49.215 --> 20:50.583
It's just rooted
in our ability to --

20:50.683 --> 20:53.853
to know what another person
is feeling.

20:53.953 --> 20:55.988
That part of your brain
is compromised --

20:56.088 --> 20:57.524
Listen, I-I, um --

20:57.624 --> 21:00.527
I'm not pulling the wings
off of flies,

21:00.627 --> 21:02.795
if that's what
you're asking.

21:02.895 --> 21:04.163
