That's him.
You're positive?

30:29.095 --> 30:30.362
Fuck, yeah, I'm positive.

30:30.462 --> 30:33.399
Because what's
a motherfucker like that

30:33.499 --> 30:34.566
doing in my neighborhood,

30:34.666 --> 30:37.669
walking with my wife,
with --

30:37.769 --> 30:39.338
**

30:39.438 --> 30:41.840
He's lucky
I couldn't get off that bus.

30:41.941 --> 30:45.111
If not, I'd be here wearing
the orange for the real deal.

30:45.211 --> 30:48.014
Hey, hey, wait.
Wait! W-What now?

30:48.114 --> 30:49.715
You-- You're gonna tell the cops
about this fucker?

30:49.815 --> 30:52.351
Y-You gonna
get me out of here or what?

30:52.451 --> 30:55.121
As we speak,
a competent Legal Aid attorney

30:55.221 --> 30:57.289
is trying to get you bail.

30:57.389 --> 30:59.091
(sighs)

30:59.191 --> 31:01.593
I might have to thank you
after all, Doc.

31:01.693 --> 31:03.629
I'm not doing this
for you.

31:03.729 --> 31:05.697
I'm doing this
for Josefa.

31:05.797 --> 31:09.301
**

31:09.401 --> 31:11.403
(voice breaking)
I did love her, you know.

31:11.503 --> 31:12.704
**

31:12.804 --> 31:14.373
Listen to me, Ronny.

31:14.473 --> 31:17.443
What you did
was unforgivable.

31:17.543 --> 31:20.112
As far as I'm concerned,
you deserve to be in here --

31:20.212 --> 31:21.313
maybe not
for killing her,

31:21.413 --> 31:22.982
but everything else.

31:23.082 --> 31:24.783
**

31:24.883 --> 31:28.554
That was not love.

31:28.654 --> 31:30.489
**

31:30.589 --> 31:32.624
(door creaks, thuds)

31:32.724 --> 31:36.462
(cellphone ringing)

31:36.562 --> 31:37.896
CHANCE: Yeah.

31:37.997 --> 31:40.132
It's Ryan Winter.

31:40.232 --> 31:41.233
I need to see you
right away.

31:41.333 --> 31:42.301
Are you okay?

31:42.401 --> 31:43.469
You sound upset.

31:43.569 --> 31:46.939
I am fucking upset!

31:47.039 --> 31:50.009
All right.
Are you at home?

31:50.109 --> 31:51.277
I'm in Pacific Heights
at the moment.

31:51.377 --> 31:53.745
I can come to you.

31:53.845 --> 31:55.681
I can't come
to your office?

31:55.781 --> 31:58.084
Why not?

31:58.184 --> 31:59.785
I feel like you don't
want me there anymore.

31:59.885 --> 32:02.321
I told you,
I'm not at the hospital.

32:02.421 --> 32:04.623
It's just easier
if I come to you.

32:07.493 --> 32:08.494
Fine.

32:08.594 --> 32:11.930
**

32:12.031 --> 32:14.333
(sighs)
I'm being fucked with.

32:14.433 --> 32:16.368
What do you mean,
"fucked with"?

32:16.468 --> 32:17.536
(sighs)

32:17.636 --> 32:19.038
Someone's
broken into my house

32:19.138 --> 32:21.773
and taken things,
moved things.

32:21.873 --> 32:23.609
**

32:23.709 --> 32:25.111
Did you call
the police?
No.

32:25.211 --> 32:26.212
It's -- It's -- It's --

32:26.312 --> 32:29.715
It's --
It's not a police matter.

32:29.815 --> 32:31.717
Well, it is
if they stole something.

32:31.817 --> 32:33.185
You should call.
No.

32:33.285 --> 32:37.356
What they stole has no value
other than to me.

32:37.456 --> 32:38.790
**

32:38.890 --> 32:41.460
I'm sorry, Ryan,
I-I don't really understand.

32:41.560 --> 32:42.995
They moved things --

32:43.095 --> 32:44.663
belongings,
possessions.

32:44.763 --> 32:47.633
They were here.
Now they are here.

32:47.733 --> 32:49.135
And before you say it,
it wasn't the housekeeper

32:49.235 --> 32:51.703
or me forgetting
where I put things.

32:51.803 --> 32:56.042
**

32:56.142 --> 32:58.344
I think it's him.

32:58.444 --> 33:00.412
**

33:00.512 --> 33:02.714
Who?

33:02.814 --> 33:06.652
Ryan, if you got a name,
you should go to the police.

33:06.752 --> 33:08.887
**

33:08.987 --> 33:11.323
He is the police.

33:11.423 --> 33:12.591
**

33:12.691 --> 33:15.561
It's Detective Kevin Hynes.

33:15.661 --> 33:16.995
He used to be SFPD,

33:17.096 --> 33:20.499
but he was transferred
to the southeast suburbs.

33:20.599 --> 33:21.733
(sighs)

33:21.833 --> 33:24.170
And I bet you he's the one
that attacked me, too.

33:24.270 --> 33:28.407
**

33:28.507 --> 33:30.842
Ryan, I-I don't mean
to dismiss what you're saying,

33:30.942 --> 33:33.245
but I'm concerned
that this might be an extension

33:33.345 --> 33:34.613
of your head trauma.

33:34.713 --> 33:36.048
It's not. It's not.
It's not.

33:36.148 --> 33:38.550
I'm telling you,
this Hynes guy,

33:38.650 --> 33:40.586
he's like...

33:40.686 --> 33:41.887
He's like a burr.
He is stuck to me.

33:41.987 --> 33:46.592
He's made it his mission in life
to hound me to my grave.

33:46.692 --> 33:48.294
(sighs shakily)

33:48.394 --> 33:51.397
I hate this.
I hate feeling weak.

33:51.497 --> 33:53.632
I hate feeling
fucking scared.

33:53.732 --> 33:54.966
I hate feeling
like a victim.

33:55.067 --> 33:56.135
I don't like it.
I don't like it.

33:56.235 --> 33:57.736
It's okay. It's okay.
It's all right.

33:57.836 --> 33:59.905
(sighs)
Come on. Just...

34:00.005 --> 34:00.939
**

34:01.039 --> 34:02.074
(exhales deeply)

34:02.174 --> 34:04.410
It's okay, Ryan.

34:04.510 --> 34:06.312
We're gonna work
through this together.

34:06.412 --> 34:08.880
You once told me
I have your trust.

34:08.980 --> 34:10.582
Is that still true?

34:10.682 --> 34:11.783
**

34:11.883 --> 34:15.921
(sighing)

34:16.021 --> 34:21.327
**

34:21.427 --> 34:25.831
When I was 8, I was standing
on a train platform

34:25.931 --> 34:28.734
in Emeryville
with my mother.

34:28.834 --> 34:32.904
And not that far from us,
there was this little boy.

34:33.004 --> 34:35.841
He was running in a circle

34:35.941 --> 34:37.176
round and round
the platform.

34:37.276 --> 34:39.311
**

34:39.411 --> 34:44.015
After a while,
we could hear the train coming.

34:44.116 --> 34:45.784
**

34:45.884 --> 34:47.119
And...

34:47.219 --> 34:49.020
**

34:49.121 --> 34:50.656
I remember the boy
still circling,

34:50.756 --> 34:55.161
you know,
as it got closer.

34:55.261 --> 34:58.130
And then...

34:58.230 --> 34:59.665
**

34:59.765 --> 35:04.303
...everyone was screaming,
and he was gone.

35:04.403 --> 35:06.138
**

35:06.238 --> 35:08.307
This woman had come
out of the crowd, grabbed him,

35:08.407 --> 35:11.210
and tossed him
in front of the train.

35:11.310 --> 35:13.979
**

35:14.079 --> 35:20.719
**

35:20.819 --> 35:25.191
**

35:25.291 --> 35:27.493
(quietly sobbing)

35:27.593 --> 35:32.864
**

35:32.964 --> 35:37.336
(high-pitched ringing)

35:37.436 --> 35:42.140
**

35:42.241 --> 35:44.543
(body thuds)

35:44.643 --> 35:46.678
(ringing stops)

35:46.778 --> 35:49.915
(breathes deeply)

35:50.015 --> 35:53.185
(sobbing continues)

35:57.989 --> 35:59.325
(breathes sharply)

36:02.728 --> 36:03.895
(sighs)

36:03.995 --> 36:06.932
It was hard.
It was really hard.

36:07.032 --> 36:08.667
(sighs)

36:08.767 --> 36:11.036
But I figured it out.

36:11.136 --> 36:12.938
I found a way

36:13.038 --> 36:17.776
to calm myself,
to cope.

36:21.713 --> 36:24.450
We should talk
about that.

36:27.686 --> 36:28.754
Some other day.

36:28.854 --> 36:31.022
Today,
I think I'm done.

36:34.960 --> 36:37.195
(keys clack)

36:37.296 --> 36:38.864
(door opens)

36:38.964 --> 36:41.733
(indistinct conversations
in distance)

36:41.833 --> 36:43.201
You're a fucking lawyer?

36:43.302 --> 36:45.904
I'm your lawyer.

36:46.004 --> 36:47.873
Chuck Haden.

36:47.973 --> 36:50.476
Dude, I...I can't pay you,
man, so...

36:50.576 --> 36:51.743
It's okay.

36:51.843 --> 36:52.811
I'm Legal Aid.

36:52.911 --> 36:55.314
I'm replacing
your public defender on this.

36:55.414 --> 36:58.417
All right, so, you --
y-you can prove I'm innocent?

36:58.517 --> 37:00.452
Oh, we got plenty
to fight 'em on,

37:00.552 --> 37:03.955
and Judge Salandrigas and I,
we surf together,

37:04.055 --> 37:05.391
so that'll count
for something.

37:05.491 --> 37:07.626
(breathes deeply)

37:07.726 --> 37:09.661
Am -- Am I getting
out of here?

37:09.761 --> 37:12.230
Yeah.
Your mom posted your bail.

37:12.331 --> 37:14.165
But the condition will be
that you stay at her place.

37:14.266 --> 37:18.670
But the important thing is
you're gonna get released, okay?

37:18.770 --> 37:19.738
But you got to be smart,
though --

37:19.838 --> 37:21.740
no drugs,
no more incidents.

37:21.840 --> 37:23.742
Well, hey, well --
You're asking me to lay low?

37:23.842 --> 37:24.743
Mm-hmm.

37:24.843 --> 37:27.679
Shit.
I know how to do that.

37:27.779 --> 37:28.747
Good.
Sign there.

37:28.847 --> 37:30.616
(pen scratches)

37:32.250 --> 37:33.919
(thudding)
(doorbell dings)

37:34.019 --> 37:35.454
(door closes)

37:35.554 --> 37:37.423
(thudding continues)

37:39.491 --> 37:40.859
(horns honking in distance)

37:40.959 --> 37:42.661
(thudding continues)

37:44.463 --> 37:47.165
(thudding continues)

37:53.605 --> 37:55.507
**

37:55.607 --> 37:58.877
(grunts)

37:58.977 --> 38:02.614
Hey.
I didn't hear you come in.

38:02.714 --> 38:04.650
You looking
for the Doc?

38:04.750 --> 38:06.151
Not here.

38:06.251 --> 38:09.054
(thudding resumes)
Figured.

38:09.154 --> 38:12.958
I tried the office.
He's not there, either.

38:13.058 --> 38:14.893
I don't know why
people carry cellphones

38:14.993 --> 38:17.162
if they're not gonna
answer them. (sniffles)

38:17.262 --> 38:18.364
(siren wailing in distance)

38:18.464 --> 38:20.165
(indistinct shouting
in distance)

38:20.265 --> 38:21.800
(sobs quietly,
sniffles)

38:21.900 --> 38:23.835
I wouldn't do that.

38:23.935 --> 38:25.971
There's no crying in here.

38:26.071 --> 38:27.473
(thudding resumes)

38:27.573 --> 38:29.174
(chuckles, sniffles)

38:29.274 --> 38:32.378
(horns honk in distance)

38:34.012 --> 38:36.548
That would hurt.

38:36.648 --> 38:37.749
That would be the idea.

38:37.849 --> 38:39.050
You ever hit a person
like that?

38:39.150 --> 38:40.251
I have.

38:40.352 --> 38:41.820
He still alive?

38:41.920 --> 38:43.188
Some of them.

38:43.288 --> 38:44.590
(thudding continues)

38:44.690 --> 38:47.926
So where do I get
one of those?

38:48.026 --> 38:49.995
What is that,
a nightstick?

38:50.095 --> 38:52.598
(breathing heavily)

38:52.698 --> 38:54.032
Depends.

38:54.132 --> 38:55.501
Why would you want one?

38:55.601 --> 38:59.070
(honking continues)

38:59.170 --> 39:00.839
(inhales deeply)

39:00.939 --> 39:04.576
(voice breaking)
There's this asshole at school

39:04.676 --> 39:08.947
who's done
some shitty stuff,

39:09.047 --> 39:11.717
bullied me or whatever.

39:11.817 --> 39:13.585
Great opportunity
for a life lesson.

39:13.685 --> 39:16.455
Anytime
somebody bullies you,

39:16.555 --> 39:19.425
you should thank them
every day.

39:19.525 --> 39:21.460
**

39:21.560 --> 39:23.562
You're joking, right?

39:23.662 --> 39:27.132
Right now, this bully is
the only person in your life

39:27.232 --> 39:30.068
who's giving you
an actual challenge.

39:30.168 --> 39:31.069
**

39:31.169 --> 39:34.440
Everybody else
is anesthetizing you,

39:34.540 --> 39:35.941
hugging the power
out of you,

39:36.041 --> 39:37.576
making you weak.

39:37.676 --> 39:41.146
You think the struggle of living
in the world gets easier,

39:41.246 --> 39:44.249
people stop giving you
a hard time?

39:44.349 --> 39:46.384
Learn
to stand up for yourself now,

39:46.485 --> 39:49.120
and give it
right back to them.

39:49.220 --> 39:50.388
Otherwise,
shut the fuck up.

39:50.489 --> 39:54.292
**

39:54.392 --> 39:55.627
(notes play)

39:55.727 --> 39:59.665
(breathing heavily)

39:59.765 --> 40:01.399
This is a baton.

40:01.500 --> 40:04.770
For your purposes,
it's probably not ideal.

40:04.870 --> 40:07.072
People will identify it
as a weapon right away.

40:07.172 --> 40:09.608
That can be a problem
down the road.

40:09.708 --> 40:14.145
Your best offense --
look around.

40:14.245 --> 40:15.914
That doorstop,
straight to the temple.

40:16.014 --> 40:18.149
Base of that lamp,
shot to the kidneys.

40:18.249 --> 40:22.320
This drawer pull over here,
great for a jab to the eye.

40:22.420 --> 40:27.826
**

40:27.926 --> 40:30.629
Anything can be a weapon.

40:30.729 --> 40:32.931
**

40:33.031 --> 40:34.365
(indistinct conversations)

40:34.466 --> 40:38.036
HYNES: We get lucky
and Ronny's alibi holds up

40:38.136 --> 40:40.138
and Lambert can put Winter
at the scene,

40:40.238 --> 40:41.439
it's only a matter of time

40:41.540 --> 40:43.942
before the shit heel
is behind bars.

40:44.042 --> 40:46.678
(glasses clinking)
(upbeat music plays on stereo)

40:46.778 --> 40:49.047
Which is good.

40:49.147 --> 40:50.782
(music continues)

40:50.882 --> 40:53.952
What's the matter with you?

40:54.052 --> 40:57.022
(conversations continue)

40:57.122 --> 40:58.524
I don't know.
I'm...

40:58.624 --> 41:00.058
(breathes sharply)

41:00.158 --> 41:02.460
I'm just starting to wonder
if that's...

41:02.561 --> 41:05.531
where Winter
ought to be.

41:05.631 --> 41:06.998
I mean, he is --

41:07.098 --> 41:08.233
you know,
he's a monster,

41:08.333 --> 41:12.804
but he's also
a deeply disturbed man.

41:12.904 --> 41:15.507
Aren't we all?

41:15.607 --> 41:17.509
Locking up the mentally ill

41:17.609 --> 41:19.678
goes against
my professional principles.

41:19.778 --> 41:24.382
Well, having him committed
goes against mine.

41:24.482 --> 41:26.885
D: Don't get excited,
but the waitress

41:26.985 --> 41:31.857
described the wing sauce
as "mischievous."

41:31.957 --> 41:34.492
Hey, D, what did you take?
Winter said --

41:34.593 --> 41:37.328
Winter said you took
something important.

41:37.428 --> 41:39.531
A rock.

41:39.631 --> 41:43.034
You took a ro--
That's what you took? A rock?

41:43.134 --> 41:45.103
HYNES:
What kind of rock?

41:45.203 --> 41:46.705
You tell me.

41:46.805 --> 41:48.840
(music continues)

41:48.940 --> 41:50.408
(conversations continue)

41:50.508 --> 41:52.711
W-Why did you take this?

41:52.811 --> 41:54.780
It was
prominently displayed.

41:54.880 --> 41:57.916
(music continues)

41:59.517 --> 42:02.721
By the way, he thinks
you're the one who broke in.

42:04.455 --> 42:06.692
Bury the lead,
why don't you?

42:06.792 --> 42:09.360
He mentioned me by name?
Yep.

42:09.460 --> 42:11.396
He also thinks you're the one
who choked him out.

42:11.496 --> 42:12.698
Get ready
for the fallout.

42:12.798 --> 42:15.634
What's one step down
from Fremont PD?

42:15.734 --> 42:16.702
Mall cop?

42:16.802 --> 42:17.903
(sighs)

42:18.003 --> 42:21.272
Did he, uh,
happen to say anything else?

42:21.372 --> 42:22.373
Yeah,
he told me a story.

42:22.473 --> 42:25.777
When he was a kid,
he was on a railway platform.

42:25.877 --> 42:27.646
He saw a woman --

42:27.746 --> 42:29.380
(music continues)

42:30.582 --> 42:33.484
He saw a woman
throw a young boy

42:33.585 --> 42:36.054
onto the tracks
in front of an oncoming train.

42:36.154 --> 42:37.555
(scoffs)

42:37.656 --> 42:41.793
Do you think that's real --
the train story?

42:41.893 --> 42:43.128
I don't know.

42:43.228 --> 42:45.731
He cried on my shoulder.

42:45.831 --> 42:47.432
Oh, Jesus Christ.

42:47.532 --> 42:49.134
(dart board thuds)
(women cheer)

42:49.234 --> 42:50.468
CHANCE: He said it happened
in Emeryville.

42:50.568 --> 42:53.338
Got to be
more than one of those.

42:53.438 --> 42:54.740
How many of them
have train stations?

42:54.840 --> 42:56.341
(clears throat)

42:56.441 --> 42:59.077
If it'll make you happy,
I can look into it.

42:59.177 --> 43:01.446
If that woman was arrested,
there --

43:01.546 --> 43:04.683
there'll be records
of that.

43:04.783 --> 43:06.952
RONNY:
They ain't got dick, man.

43:07.052 --> 43:08.954
They had to let me walk.

43:09.054 --> 43:10.856
No, I'm staying
at my mom's place.

43:10.956 --> 43:12.958
(exhales sharply)
Yeah.

43:13.058 --> 43:15.994
Social Services is coming
tomorrow to check on the kids.
(door opens)

43:16.094 --> 43:18.129
Yeah, they --

43:19.931 --> 43:21.132
(lighter clicks)

43:21.232 --> 43:24.803
Yeah, um...
Mm.

43:24.903 --> 43:28.039
As long as I get to see them,
dude, that's what's --

43:29.841 --> 43:32.878
**

43:32.978 --> 43:36.882
Um...hold on, man.

43:36.982 --> 43:38.049
**

43:38.149 --> 43:39.184
No, no, no, no, no.

43:39.284 --> 43:40.618
I'm gonna call you back.

43:40.719 --> 43:42.287
Yeah,
I'm gonna call you back, man.

43:42.387 --> 43:43.789
(grunts)

43:43.889 --> 43:48.694
(screaming)

43:48.794 --> 43:50.495
(loud thud,
screaming stops)

43:50.595 --> 43:54.365
**

43:57.703 --> 43:59.170
**

43:59.270 --> 44:01.539
CHANCE:
What are you talking about?

44:01.639 --> 44:03.875
It was the middle of the day.

44:03.975 --> 44:06.011
There are no witnesses?
HYNES: None.

44:06.111 --> 44:09.180
That's why it's easy for them
to call it a suicide.

44:09.280 --> 44:10.181
One thing for sure

44:11.182 --> 44:14.552
is SFPD is gonna say
Josefa's case is now open,

44:14.652 --> 44:15.721
but solved.

44:15.821 --> 44:18.256
Solved?
That is fucking bullshit.

44:18.356 --> 44:19.324
**

44:19.424 --> 44:20.525
What they mean
is they have a guy,

44:21.760 --> 44:23.494
and they don't need to waste
any more tax dollars looking.

44:23.594 --> 44:25.430
And Winter is off the hook
again.

44:25.530 --> 44:28.566
Welcome
to my fucking world.

44:28.666 --> 44:30.435
**

44:30.535 --> 44:32.070
(sighs)

44:32.170 --> 44:35.173
(gate whirring)

44:37.776 --> 44:40.278
(birds chirping)

44:40.378 --> 44:42.613
(whirring continues)

45:05.270 --> 45:08.639
It really freaked him out,
what you did.

45:10.108 --> 45:12.443
I talked him down.

45:12.543 --> 45:13.979
He couldn't explain
why all of a sudden

45:14.079 --> 45:16.114
I was moving
all of his shit around.

45:16.214 --> 45:18.784
(vehicle passes)

45:18.884 --> 45:20.451
Can you?

45:22.653 --> 45:23.922
Look,
I don't give a shit,

45:24.022 --> 45:25.791
but I can't lose
this job.

45:25.891 --> 45:27.258
I'm the only one
that's gonna be around

45:27.358 --> 45:28.994
to take care
of this kid.

45:29.094 --> 45:30.762
(dog barking in distance)

45:30.862 --> 45:34.132
Just don't do it again.

45:37.002 --> 45:40.305
In case you get hungry.

45:40.405 --> 45:42.640
Hope you like mustard.

45:42.740 --> 45:44.142
Hey.

45:44.242 --> 45:48.613
Why didn't you scream
when you saw me in the house?

45:50.348 --> 45:52.583
'Cause you're not scary.

45:53.919 --> 45:56.687
(footsteps)

45:56.788 --> 45:58.323
(door opens)

45:58.423 --> 46:01.026
KIRSTEN: Memorial for Josefa
will be held tomorrow.

46:01.126 --> 46:02.794
I know not all of you
knew her,

46:02.894 --> 46:05.030
but it would send
a strong message of support

46:05.130 --> 46:07.632
if you could get as many staff
members as possible

46:07.732 --> 46:09.200
to the services.

46:09.300 --> 46:10.701
Also, it would be nice

46:10.802 --> 46:13.872
if we could set up a fund
for Josefa's children.

46:13.972 --> 46:17.642
And finally,
I just spoke with SFPD,

46:17.742 --> 46:19.477
and the rumors are true --

46:19.577 --> 46:23.148
Apparently, her husband
committed suicide today.

46:23.248 --> 46:24.715
Though it might sound
like justice...

46:24.816 --> 46:26.351
What's going on?

46:26.451 --> 46:27.886
...it's simply
more violence.

46:27.986 --> 46:31.890
Maybe read a memo
once in a while.

46:31.990 --> 46:33.058
You could've had cake.

46:33.158 --> 46:35.126
For what?

46:35.226 --> 46:39.230
Ryan Winter just donated
$1 million to the unit...

46:39.330 --> 46:42.000
in Josefa's name.

46:42.100 --> 46:44.402
**

46:44.502 --> 46:46.637
Jesus.

46:46.737 --> 46:49.640
(indistinct conversations)

46:49.740 --> 46:54.812
**

46:54.913 --> 46:59.017
KIRSTEN: We're all too familiar
with violence here.

46:59.117 --> 47:00.886
Josefa struggled with it daily.

47:00.986 --> 47:02.820
**

47:02.921 --> 47:06.892
The fact that she was making
such great progress

47:06.992 --> 47:09.727
only to fall victim
once again

47:09.827 --> 47:12.864
makes it
all the more devastating.

47:12.964 --> 47:16.001
To lose Josefa,
especially in this way,

47:16.101 --> 47:19.270
is traumatic for us all.

47:19.370 --> 47:20.738
Here, we try to find safety
in each other

47:20.838 --> 47:24.175
as a first step
in finding safety in the world.

47:24.275 --> 47:25.877
Hey, take a bow.

47:25.977 --> 47:28.579
Your good work
made this happen.

47:28.679 --> 47:32.783
**

47:32.884 --> 47:35.887
(quiet laughter)

47:35.987 --> 47:40.858
**

47:40.959 --> 47:42.093
(chuckles)

47:42.193 --> 47:44.029
(chuckles)

47:44.129 --> 47:47.432
**

47:47.532 --> 47:49.767
Luckily,
there are people out there,

47:49.867 --> 47:51.236
like Mr. Winter,

47:51.336 --> 47:53.238
who make it possible
for us to heal those in need

47:53.338 --> 47:57.108
through their generosity.

47:57.208 --> 48:01.479
I know
this is a time for grief,

48:01.579 --> 48:05.316
but on behalf of Josefa,
I'd like to thank you.

48:05.416 --> 48:07.752
(applause)

48:07.852 --> 48:09.620
**

48:09.720 --> 48:16.227
**

48:16.327 --> 48:18.763
(chuckles)

48:18.863 --> 48:21.399
**

48:21.499 --> 48:22.633
-Oh.
-Oh!

48:22.733 --> 48:24.936
(whimpers)

48:25.036 --> 48:27.105
Thank you.

48:27.205 --> 48:31.742
**

48:31.842 --> 48:35.746
(high-pitched ringing)

48:35.846 --> 48:39.484
**

48:42.853 --> 48:44.155
**

48:44.255 --> 48:47.425
* None of us seems fine

48:47.525 --> 48:49.927
**

48:50.028 --> 48:54.932
* None of us is good

48:55.033 --> 48:57.435
**

48:57.535 --> 48:59.937
* Most of us are nice

49:00.038 --> 49:03.708
**

49:03.808 --> 49:09.981
* When we feel
we really should be *

49:10.081 --> 49:11.216
**

49:11.316 --> 49:14.986
* Nice won't get us far

49:15.086 --> 49:17.488
**

49:17.588 --> 49:22.493
* 'Cause none of us is fine

